##You bless me

WECHAT denganqing1984

Feature description, here, I will share my writing, reading the book.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
When I woke up in the morning, I felt my eyes were swollen and my body was tired. My mother yelled for me to get up for dinner many times downstairs, and I didn't have the strength to say yes. My mother later described her mood, "you get up very early every day, today after eight o'clock, you haven't got up, my heart sank. " I immediately understand that my mother worried about whether I was infected.

After all, I came back from Wuhan. After all, there are so many infected people now... I'm not sure if it's true, but another voice has been obstinately sounded: "Don't think too much, this is the common cold. " Every New Year, I will come home with a cold, this year of course is no exception.

Long-term living in Beijing, accustomed to the life of heating, a sudden return to the south, the body is not very well adapted. It's normal to have a cold. That's what I tell myself. Back home, I once described it this way:

"Go to my hometown by the Yangtze River. It's the cold of a bitter woman. She doesn't scratch you with the claws of the wind or scold you with dry words. She doesn't even look at you. She just sits in the back of the room and doesn't talk. But you can feel her everywhere, every brick crevice permeates her wet and cold heart, every thin water drop in the air is the tears she secretly shed. You can't get rid of it. At night, when you sleep, her hand rubs against your face, peeks through your flesh, rubs against your bones. You Shiver with cold, and her breath runs down your neck."

And My mother never understood why I was so afraid of the cold, Wu Wu warm baby, wearing a layer after layer, reading the leg still covered with a thin quilt, the result or a cold. She is always busy, washing this brush that, back sweat on a towel stuffed, and I freeze shrink, like a poor stray dog.

Finally get up to eat, mother has helped me Sheng sweet potato porridge, and I have no appetite, smell the cooking oil and salt smell, immediately want to vomit. I swallowed my nausea and ate two bowls of porridge before coming upstairs. Sitting on the bed, drowsy.

Mother came into the room, I was ready to take off clothes, she immediately said: "You do not sleep, I burned Qingai water, you soak feet to sleep. " I said good, mother went downstairs again. Outside the window for many days of continuous continuous winter rain, the windowpanes knot water, the wind from the cracks in the windows to kill in, wrapped in the biting cold. I shivered again.

What if I do have an infection? I can't stop thinking about it. First of all, I must have hurt the whole family, because we live so close together every day. One more. How do I get to the hospital? It's said to be overcrowded. How can I avoid cross-contamination? I only have a one-time mask, bought online and sent by friends, are not sent to the countryside, not to mention the city has been closed..

A lot of real-life problems came up. At last, I thought I might die, didn't I? The lungs are invaded by the virus, breathing is difficult, every organ of the body is damaged... all these thoughts make me afraid.

When I woke up in the morning, I felt my eyes were swollen and my body was tired. My mother yelled for me to get up for dinner many times downstairs, and I didn't have the strength to say yes. A lot of real-life problems came up. At last, I thought I might die, didn't I? The lungs are invaded by the virus, breathing is difficult, every organ of the body is damaged... all these thoughts make me afraid.

Thinking about it, my mother came up with a plastic bucket filled with scalding Ai Qing water. Mother first with a towel to help me wipe my back and neck, let me change a underwear; blue moxa water into the foot basin to let me soak at the same time, my mother took ginger to wipe my hands and feet. She wiped it and looked at me with concern.

I managed to smile: "Nothing. It should be a cold. " She "Um" ground, squat down to rub my feet. I said, "I'll come by myself. " My mother wouldn't let me, so she patiently tried the temperature of the water and added a little hot water. Once again I said, "I'll come by myself. " My mother squeezed my feet and gently rubbed them. "When my feet are warm, my body is warm. I'll sleep it off. " After I washed my feet and went to bed, she tucked me in and covered me with a thin blanket so the air wouldn't leak.

As soon as I lay down, I fell asleep almost immediately. When I opened my eyes again, it was still raining outside. My body feels refreshed, my energy is back, and I'm hungry. It seems that I really just have a cold, can not help but relieved. Coming down to the kitchen, mother cooked another meal. I ate two big bowls in one sitting. My mother was relieved.

I suddenly remembered the year before a cold and fever, many days bad, to the village health station hit a few bottles of intravenous injection, or not improved. I didn't recover until the day before I left, I had a few more i.v.s, and I was sweating. Later I found out that my mother had gone behind my back to ask the woman next door, who said it was my aunt who had just died and was haunting me. My mother burned a piece of paper and said a prayer, and I was spared.

I think this time she probably went to do it again, and asked her, she acquiesced. I laughed again and asked, "which ancestor is it this time? " My mother said, "you don't care about this, it's fine now. " I laughed at my mother's superstition, mother quickly drank and stopped: "Don't talk nonsense! The Bodhisattva always protects you. " I smiled back: "that you are the Bodhisattva, you protect me. " Mother laughed and scolded: "You don't talk nonsense, if I have this ability, you won't get sick. "
